───────────┴────────────┐                       │\n│              │     BaseStra
tegy        │                       │\n│              │    (Abstract Class)     
│                       │\n│              └────────────┬────────────┘           
           │\n│                           │                                     
│\n│     ┌─────────────────────┼─────────────────────┐              │\n│     │  
                  │                     │              │\n│     ▼               
     ▼                     ▼              │\n│ ┌─────────┐        ┌────────────┐
       ┌──────────┐         │\n│ │Longshot │        │  Economic  │        │ Arbi
trage│         │\n│ │ Fading  │        │  Momentum  │        │          │       
 │\n│ └─────────┘        └────────────┘        └──────────┘         │\n└────────
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                    
         │\n                              ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────
───────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Strategy Runner          
                   │\n│  - Fetches market data from Kalshi API                  
       │\n│  - Runs all active strategies                                   │\n│
 - Executes orders (paper/live)                                 │\n│  - Updates 
positions & P&L                                      │\n└───────────────────────
──────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## Signal Generation 
Module\n\n### Signal Interface\n\n```typescript\ninterface Signal {\n  marketId:
string;        // Market ticker symbol\n  direction: "buy_yes" | "buy_no" | "sel
l_yes" | "sell_no";\n  confidence: number;      // 0-1 probability of success\n 
edge: number;            // Expected edge in cents (0-100)\n  strategy: string; 
      // Strategy name\n  timestamp: Date;\n  metadata: object;        // Strate
gy-specific context\n}\n```\n\n### Built-in Strategies\n\n#### 1. Longshot Fadin
g Strategy\n\nBased on Charlie\'s research on favorite-longshot bias.\n\n**Logic
:**\n- Target markets: Weather, Entertainment, Culture (niche categories)\n- Pri
ce range: YES contracts priced 5¢-20¢\n- Action: Sell YES (bet against longshots
)\n\n**Edge Calculation:**\n```\noverpricingFactor = (20 - price) / 15\nedge = p
rice * 0.15 * overpricingFactor\nconfidence = 0.7 + (0.25 * overpricingFactor)\n
```\n\n**Research Basis:** UCD/GWU 2025 study showing 5-20¢ contracts lose ~60% 
of invested capital due to retail overpricing of tail-risk events.\n\n#### 2. Ec
onomic Momentum Strategy\n\nTrades scheduled macro markets using pre-release inf
ormation edge.\n\n**Logic:**\n- Target markets: Economics, Finance categories\n-
Trigger: Divergence > 8 percentage points between Kalshi implied probability and
high-quality forecast\n- Action: Trade in direction of forecast\n\n**Edge Calcul
ation:**\n```\ndivergence = |impliedProb - forecastProb| * 100\nedge = divergenc
e * 0.5\nconfidence = 0.5 + (divergence / 100)\n```\n\n**Data Sources:** Atlanta
Fed Nowcast, Cleveland Fed, private surveys\n\n#### 3. Arbitrage Strategy\n\nExp
loits cross-platform pricing divergences.\n\n**Logic:**\n- Monitor identical eve
nts across platforms (Kalshi vs Polymarket)\n- Trigger: Spread > 3 cents after f
ees\n- Action: Buy on cheaper platform, sell on expensive\n\n**Edge Calculation:
**\n```\nedge = spread - estimatedFees (where estimatedFees ≈ 2¢)\n```\n\n---\n\
n## Position Sizing Module\n\n### Kelly Criterion Implementation\n\nThe framewor
k uses the Kelly Criterion for optimal position sizing:\n\n```\nf* = (bp - q) / 
b\n\nWhere:\n  b = odds received = (100 - price) / price\n  p = probability of w
in (from signal confidence)\n  q = probability of loss = 1 - p\n```\n\n### Safet
y Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Default | Description |\n|-----------|---------|--
-----------|\n| `kellyFraction` | 0.25 | Quarter Kelly for safety |\n| `maxPosit
ionPct` | 0.05 | Max 5% of portfolio per trade |\n| `minContracts` | 1 | Minimum
trade size |\n| `maxContracts` | 1000 | Maximum trade size |\n\n### Example Calc
ulation\n\n```javascript\n// Market: YES trading at 15¢\n// Signal confidence: 8
0%\n// Portfolio: $10,000\n\nb = (100 - 15) / 15 = 5.67\np = 0.80\nq = 0.20\n\nk
ellyFull = (5.67 * 0.80 - 0.20) / 5.67 = 0.765\nkellyAdjusted = 0.765 * 0.25 = 0
.191\n\npositionValue = $10,000 * 0.191 = $1,910\nriskPerContract = 15¢ = $0.15\
ncontracts = $1,910 / $0.15 = 12,733 → capped at 1,000\n\nFinal: 1,000 contracts
, risking $150 (1.5% of portfolio)\n```\n\n---\n\n## P&L Tracking Module\n\n### 
Features\n\n- **Real-time P&L**: Tracks both realized and unrealized P&L\n- **Po
sition tracking**: Full position lifecycle management\n- **Performance metrics**
: Sharpe ratio, max drawdown, win rate\n- **Equity curve**: Historical portfolio
value over time\n- **Daily aggregation**: Daily P&L breakdown\n\n### Performance
Metrics\n\n| Metric | Formula |\n|--------|---------|\n| Win Rate | `winningTrad
es / totalTrades` |\n| Sharpe Ratio | `(avgDailyReturn / stdDev) * √252` |\n| Ma
x Drawdown | `max(peak - trough)` |\n| Total Return | `(current - initial) / ini
tial` |\n\n### Example Output\n\n```javascript\n{\n  strategyName: "LongshotFadi
ng",\n  totalTrades: 150,\n  winningTrades: 95,\n  losingTrades: 55,\n  winRate:
0.633,\n  totalPnl: 12500,  // $125.00\n  avgTradeReturn: 83.3,\n  sharpeRatio: 
1.85,\n  maxDrawdown: 2100,\n  maxDrawdownPct: 0.021,\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Integ
ration with Bob\'s API\n\n### Data Flow\n\n```\n┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────
────┐     ┌──────────────┐\n│   Kalshi     │────▶│  Bob\'s API   │────▶│  Strate
gies  │\n│   Exchange   │     │   Client     │     │              │\n└──────────
────┘     └──────────────┘     └──────────────┘\n                               
                │\n                                                ▼\n          
                              ┌──────────────┐\n                                
        │  Order Mgmt  │\n                                         │  (Paper/Liv
e)│\n                                         └──────────────┘\n```\n\n### API E
ndpoints Used\n\n| Endpoint | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|\n| `GET /markets
` | Fetch active markets |\n| `GET /markets/:ticker/orderbook` | Get bid/ask pri
ces |\n| `POST /orders` | Submit orders (live trading) |\n| `GET /positions` | T
rack open positions |\n\n### Rate Limiting\n\nThe framework respects Kalshi\'s r
ate limits (100 requests per 10 seconds) through Bob\'s built-in rate limiter.\n
\n---\n\n## Usage\n\n### Basic Usage\n\n```javascript\nconst { StrategyRunner } 
= require("./backend/strategies/runner");\n\nconst runner = new StrategyRunner({
\n  apiKey: process.env.KALSHI_API_KEY,\n  demo: true,              // Paper tra
ding\n  initialCapital: 100000,  // $1,000 in cents\n  pollIntervalMs: 60000,   
