ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='Now I see the issue! The mock_pool returns empty arrays for `strategy
_trades` and `strategy_positions_view` queries. When PnLTracker tries to calcula
te PnL:\n\n1. `getUnrealizedPnL` queries `strategy_positions_view` - gets empty 
rows, returns 0\n2. `getRealizedPnL` queries `strategy_trades` - gets empty rows
, returns 0\n3. `getTotalPnL` returns `{ realized: 0, unrealized: 0, total: 0 }`
\n4. `getWinRate` queries `strategy_trades` with `attributed_pnl` filter - gets 
empty rows\n5. `getTradesToday` queries `strategy_trades` - gets empty rows\n\nB
ut the error is `"Cannot read properties of undefined (reading \'unrealized_pnl\
')"`. This suggests the error is happening somewhere else. Let me look at how th
e `/api/strategies/:id/pnl` endpoint uses the PnLTracker in the server code, and
specifically how it interacts with MockPool.\n\nActually, wait - the error might
be in the PnLTracker itself when it tries to access `result.rows[0].unrealized_p
nl` but `result.rows[0]` is undefined because the query returns no rows in a dif
ferent code path.\n\nLet me trace through the PnLTracker code with MockPool:\n\n
`getUnrealizedPnL`:\n```js\nconst result = await client.query(\n  `SELECT COALES
CE(SUM(calculated_unrealized_pnl), 0) as unrealized_pnl FROM strategy_positions_
view WHERE strategy_id = $1`,\n  [strategyId]\n);\nreturn parseInt(result.rows[0
].unrealized_pnl || 0);\n```\n\nWith MockPool, `q.includes("from strategy_positi
ons_view")` is true, so it returns `{ rows: [] }`. Then `result.rows[0]` is `und
efined`, and `result.rows[0].unrealized_pnl` throws the error!\n\nSimilarly, `ge
tRealizedPnL` would also fail because `strategy_trades` returns `{ rows: [] }`.\
n\nSo the bug is in MockPool - it should return at least one row with the expect
ed columns for these queries, or the PnLTracker should handle empty rows.\n\nThe
simplest fix is to update MockPool to return a row with `unrealized_pnl: 0` for 
`strategy_positions_view` queries, and `realized_pnl: 0` for `strategy_trades` q
ueries when the strategy_id matches.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the 
mock_pool.js code:\n\n```js\nif (q.includes("from strategy_positions_view")) {\n
 return { rows: [] };\n}\n```\n\nFor `getUnrealizedPnL`, the query is:\n```sql\n
SELECT COALESCE(SUM(calculated_unrealized_pnl), 0) as unrealized_pnl\nFROM strat
egy_positions_view\nWHERE strategy_id = $1\n```\n\nMockPool should return `{ row
s: [{ unrealized_pnl: 0 }] }` for this query.\n\nFor `getRealizedPnL`, the query
is:\n```sql\nSELECT COALESCE(SUM(attributed_pnl), 0) as realized_pnl\nFROM strat
egy_trades st\nJOIN trades t ON st.trade_id = t.id\nWHERE st.strategy_id = $1 AN
D t.traded_at >= $2 AND t.traded_at <= $3\n```\n\nMockPool should return `{ rows
: [{ realized_pnl: 0 }] }`.\n\nFor `getWinRate`, the query is:\n```sql\nSELECT C
OUNT(*) as total_trades, COUNT(*) FILTER (WHERE attributed_pnl > 0) as winning_t
rades, COUNT(*) FILTER (WHERE attributed_pnl < 0) as losing_trades\nFROM strateg
y_trades\nWHERE strategy_id = $1 AND attributed_pnl IS NOT NULL\n```\n\nMockPool
should return `{ rows: [{ total_trades: 0, winning_trades: 0, losing_trades: 0 }
] }`.\n\nFor `getTradesToday`, the query is:\n```sql\nSELECT COUNT(*) as trades_
today FROM strategy_trades WHERE strategy_id = $1 AND recorded_at >= CURRENT_DAT
E\n```\n\nMockPool should return `{ rows: [{ trades_today: 0 }] }`.\n\nThis is a
clear bug in Bob\'s MockPool. As Dave, I should fix it since it\'s blocking Char
lie\'s frontend integration. Let me make these fixes to Bob\'s mock_pool.js.\n\n
I also need to add an aggregate `/api/strategies/pnl` endpoint to Bob\'s server.
